cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the challenge of analyzing Twitter messages which contain misspellings, elisions, and grammatical errors. This falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) since the goal is to make sense of the data. The paper also discusses various techniques for processing the raw data, which could fall under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) since it involves developing techniques for processing and normalizing text data.
